README

1. 
To run the simulator, you have to first build Irrlicht
	-cd into RoboSub/Simulator/irrlicht-1.8.3/source/Irrlicht
	-make
	-check below for fixes for some common errors

2.
Make RoboSub (in Qt Creater)

3.
Move the assets folder into your build directory 
	-build directory is in Qt Creater under Projects (on the left side), build directory
	-assets folder is in the Simulator/ folder

4.
Move the settings folder in src/ to your build directory

5.
You should be able to run simulator now


Common Errors

	-Missing openGl
		-sudo apt-get install mesa-utils
	-Missing GL/gl.h
		-sudo apt-get install mesa-common-dev
	-Cannot find -lGL or -lGLU
		-read http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18406369/qt-cant-find-lgl-error
		TLDR (might not always work)
		-sudo ln -s /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/mesa/libGL.so.1 /usr/lib/libGL.so
		-sudo ln -s /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/mesa/libGLU.so.1 /usr/lib/libGLU.so